#: ../../O/overclock.rst:5
msgid "overclock"
msgstr "overclock"

#: ../../O/overclock.rst:7
msgid "/oh´vr·klok´/, vt\\."
msgstr "/oh´vr·klok´/, 他動詞"

#: ../../O/overclock.rst:9
msgid ""
"To operate a CPU or other digital logic device at a rate higher than it was "
"designed for, under the assumption that the manufacturer put some "
":ref:`slop` into the specification to account for manufacturing tolerances. "
"Overclocking something can result in intermittent :ref:`crash`\\es, and can "
"even burn things out, since power dissipation is directly proportional to "
":ref:`clock` frequency. People who make a hobby of this are sometimes called"
" \"overclockers\"; they are thrilled that they can run their CPU a few "
"percent faster, even though they can only tell the difference by running a "
":ref:`benchmark` program. See also :ref:`case-mod`\\."
msgstr ""
"CPUやその他のデジタル論理デバイスを、メーカーが製造公差を考慮して仕様にいくらかの\\ :ref:`slop`\\ "
"を入れているという前提のもとで、設計された速度より高い速度で動作させること。何かをオーバークロックすると、断続的な\\ :ref:`crash`\\ "
"が起こることがあり、消費電力は\\ :ref:`clock`\\ "
"周波数に正比例するため、物を焼き切ることさえある。これを趣味にする人々は時に\"overclockers\"と呼ばれる。彼らはCPUを数パーセント速く動かせることに胸を躍らせるが、その違いは\\"
" :ref:`benchmark`\\ プログラムを走らせることでしか分からない。\\ :ref:`case-mod`\\ も参照。"
